> If you're like us, three little words have the power to transform an ordinary day into an extraordinary day: Breakfast. For. Dinner. This week, we're serving up one of our "brinner" favorites: a fully-loaded potato hash. Chunks of Yukon Golds, bell pepper, and onion are roasted until tender and lightly charred, then topped with cheesy fried eggs, pico de gallo, and smoky red pepper crema. Load up a little bit of everything on your fork, then dig right in!

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}; dice remaining onion into 1-inch pieces.

Toss potatoes, bell pepper, and diced onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets.) Season with @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt and @pepper.

Roast on top rack (top and middle racks for 4) until potatoes are golden brown and softened, and bell pepper and onion are lightly charred at the edges, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Pico de Gallo ==

Meanwhile, finely dice @Roma tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, half the cilantro, and jalapeño to taste. Add half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{¼%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt and @pepper; stir to combine.

== Pickled Onion ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine sliced onion, remaining vinegar, @sugar{¼%teaspoon}, and @salt{¼%teaspoon}. Stir to combine. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

== Cheesy Fried Eggs ==

When veggies have about 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper.

When eggs have about ~{1%minute} left, sprinkle each with @Mexican cheese blend{½%cup}; cover pan to melt cheese.

Remove pan from heat.

== Assembly ==

Once veggies are done, season with salt and pepper.

Divide potato hash between plates; top with cheesy fried eggs, pico de gallo, pickled onion, and @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoon}. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro if desired and serve.